postcontent:
To commemorate the service the NRA has performed in fighting for our 2nd Amendment rights; 

Charles Daly, in conjunction with the National Rifle Association, is proud to present a limited edition production of a NRA "Winchester" 1892 lever action rifle and a "Colt" 1873 single action revolver. Both chambered in .45 LC. Available here as one of a very limited offering of only 250 sets with matching serial numbers. Both, the Rifle and Pistol, in this set, are serialized as "NRA01024" 


These fine replica firearms are manufactured in Italy to exacting standards by the American cowboy shooters. A portion of the proceeds from the sale of these firearms will go toward the Charles Daly Youth Endowment at the NRA. 

Here's your chance to get a piece of American history with a price and quality only Charles Daly can provide. 

Only 1,000 rifles and 5,000 revolvers will be built in this Limited Edition;

With the first 250 rifles and revolvers sold together as a matched serialized set packed in an "old west" hardwood carrying case. 

1892 Lever Action Rifle

This beautiful replica of the 1892 Winchester rifle has become one of the most popular lever action rifles of all time. Designed by John M. Browning, the 1892 was considered one of the finest and was one of the most sought after rifles of its day. 

This fine replica is being produced by ArmiSport in Italy. ArmiSport is among the finest manufacturers of replica firearms in the world. The craftsmanship and the attention to detail can be seen in each and every rifle they produce.

Features and Specifications:

Calibers .45LC, in a 24¼" octagonal barrel front dovetail and rear adjustable sights 

Special takedown feature that enables the rifle to be broken down into two easily transportable pieces 

Color case hardened receiver with special gold NRA logo engraved and inlaid in the receiver 

Oil finished Turkish walnut stock and forend with color case hardened crescent buttplate and forend cap 

Special NRA serial numbers assigned to each firearm 

1873 Single Action Revolver 

The 1873 single action revolver is one of the most popular and one of the most recognizable firearms in American history. Originally designed by Samuel Colt, this revolver has stood the test of time. This fine replica is being produced for Charles Daly by F.LLI Pietta in Italy. It is easy to see why these single action revolvers have been so successful. The unsurpassed quality and the beautiful finish are the trademarks of Pietta. 

Features and Specifications:

Chambered in .45LC, 4¾" barrel with front blade sight 

Color case hardened receiver with brass backstrap and trigger guard 

High polish blue barrel and cylinder 

Simulated ivory grips with special gold NRA medallion 

Special NRA serial numbers assigned to each firearm 

NRA Limited Edition Rifle and Revolver in Wooden Case (Matching Serial Numbers) 

These fine firearms are NEW IN BOX. They come with the Charles Daly warranty and manuel IN ALL ORIGINAL BOXES AND with the "old west" hardwood carrying CASE.

title: For Sale:  Rossi .38 Special 5-Shot Revolver
postcontent:
This is a Rossi revolver chambered in .38 Special.  It is an older pistol, I believe it may be a predecessor to the Rossi Model 68.  The Rossi Model 68's were made in Brazil and imported by Interarms, where as this is branded by the Garcia Corporation.  I'm not a historian so I don't really know any more about this model.  One interesting thing is the serial number is on the bottom of the grip, instead of on the side like the 1980's era Rossis.  

There is a moderate amount of wear but that is to be expected on an older revolver such as this one.  In my opinion the worn steel gives this gun added "character".  The internals are great.  Action is tight, and timing is like clockwork.  Patterns nicely for a small revolver like this one.

This gun is really fun to shoot.

  This would make a great truck gun or something to toss in the tackle box, or for home defense on a budget.  Price is somewhat negotiable, send me an offer and I'll get back to you as soon as I can.

Thanks
